 \frac{1}{x} + \frac{1}{y} = \frac{1}{n!} \Rightarrow x = \frac{n!y}{y-n!}
  x \in \Bbb Z^+ \Rightarrow y-n! \mid n!y = n!y - n!^2 + n!^2 = n!(y-n!) + n!^2 \Rightarrow y - n! \mid n!^2
